description:
Mister No rebels against the criminals with whom he had involuntarily collaborated and he follows them all the way to Paraguay, in a fight in which he’s determined not to give up. But in the meantime the police are already after him because they believe he is an accomplice of the robbers. Jerry finds himself caught in the crossfire!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 21 released on February, 1991.
name: Colpo Grosso

description:
In a little street in Caracas, Mister No sees his old fellow solider Collins die in a mysterious way. A photo from the wallet of Collins leads him to Haiti. A nightmare reveals the enigma: his friend was killed by means of a voodoo ritual!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 22 released on March, 1991.
name: Destinazione Haiti

description:
In Haiti, Mister No meets Collins’ girlfriend, the beautiful Geneviève, who is conducting a relentless fight against Colonel Kovac’s ferocious “Tontons Macoutes” together with her guerrillas. Kovacs orders the witch Mama Mathilda to cast a spell on Mister No!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 23 released on April, 1991.
name: L'Isola della Magia

description:
The rich Mister Murphy, Mister No’s new client, is a keen angler who’s eager for thrills and adventure. Jerry therefore advises him to follow the legendary Jangadeiros, the Brazilian fishermen of the North-East, who use a small, primitive vessel, the Jangada. But an international company, the Atlantic, is planning to organize fishing industrially and wants to destroy the Jangadeiros!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 24 released on May, 1991.
name: Atlantico!

description:
The fishing expedition with Mister Murphy and Stelio the Jangadeiro ends in a unpredictable manner. An Atlantic battleship rams them and our men have to contend with sharks. By now the conflict has turned into a full-blown war between the Atlantic and the Jangadeiros and Mister No decides to challenge Johnny Columbus, the president of the company, on his own territory…

"Tutto Mister No" n. 25 released on June, 1991.
name: Bersaglio Umano

description:
Bitter war is being waged between Mister No, who is defending the Jangadeiros, and Atlantic. Jerry steals a lorry from the company, eliminates the killers sent by Johnny Columbus to kill him and infiltrates the crook’s villa to find out more about his shady trafficking…

"Tutto Mister No" n. 26 released on July, 1991.
name: La Furia Gialla

description:
A millionaire Venezuelan, Roberto Galindo, promotes a sort of competition between private police: the first one to bring back his nephew Carlos Gomez will receive a prize of twenty thousand dollars. Mister No joins detective Brandao in the quest, which at first promises to be fruitful. But the matter takes a different course and Brandao’s mission turns out to be very different….

"Tutto Mister No" n. 27 released on August, 1991.
name: Chi ha Visto Carlos Gomez?

description:
Carlos Gomez is, in reality, the ex-fiancé of Cristina, Galindo’s wife. Galindo wants to have him killed because he has always been jealous of Carlos. Cristina decides to look for Carlos, to save his life. Too many - among whom the ruthless Pepe Uranga - are lured by the sum Galindo has put on Carlos Gomez’s head, but the latter has a guardian angel: Mister No!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 28 released on September, 1991.
name: Diamanti

description:
An emergency landing in the heart of the Amazonian forest leads Mister No to discover a mysterious paper mâché town, similar to a movie set. The inhabitants of the city try to eliminate him, but Jerry survives and the CIA contacts him. Subsequently, a beautiful heiress, Delia Norris, approaches him but she dies in his arms….

"Tutto Mister No" n. 29 released on October, 1991.
name: La Città Misteriosa

description:
Mister No discovers that a square of Buenos Aires has been reproduced in the jungle, identical to the one in which an important political summit is about to take place in the Argentinean capital. The right-wing extremists prepare an attack on the opposition leaders. But Mister No will have another bitter surprise….

"Tutto Mister No" n. 30 released on November, 1991.
name: Doppio Gioco

description:
Guided by the ruthless El Loco, the terrible Colombian outlaws known as the Bandoleros burst into Bogotà airport and commandeer two aeroplanes. One of these, however, is Mister No’s Piper. He hunts down the Bandoleros to recover it, helped by the beautiful Beatriz..

"Tutto Mister No" n. 31 released on December, 1991.
name: El Loco

description:
Negi Springfield is ten years old . . . and a powerful wizard! This boy wizard is the greatest prodigy ever to graduate from his magic school in England. After graduation, however, Negi’s given an unusual assignment: teach English at an all-girl school in Japan. Now Negi has to find a way to deal with his thirty-one totally gorgeous–and completely overaffectionate–students . . . without using magic! Based on the Negima! anime, this is a fresh take on the beloved Negima! story.

Includes special extras after the story!

Chapter Titles

  • 1st Period: Untitled
  • 2nd Period: Everyone's Names and Attendance Records!
  • 3rd Period: My Student Is A Vampire!?
  • 4th Period: Untitled
  • Mahora Sentai Baka Rangers Chapter 7: Enter the New Sixth Character!!
name: Boy Wizard!

description:
Negi Springfield is a boy wizard who teaches English at an all-girl school in Japan. The school has never shown indications of being haunted, but suddenly there are disturbing signs of a visiting spirit: a strange voice, piano music in an empty room, and sightings of a ghostly white figure. Could one of Negi’s adorable students actually be a ghost? Based on the Negima! anime, this is a fresh take on the beloved Negima! story.

Includes special extras after the story!

Chapter Titles

  • 5th Period: So My Last Student Is A Ghost?
  • 6th Period: Fortune-Telling Is Konoka-san's Specialty!
  • 7th Period: A Knight's Duty To Protect The Princess!
  • 8th Period: Leave The Book-Finding To The Library Exploration Club!
  • 9th Period: My Childhood Friend Is Here!
  • Special Period: Mahora Sentai Baka Rangers
name: Haunted School?

description:
Negi Springfield is a ten-year-old boy wizard with big dreams: He hopes to become a great wizard like his father, the legendary Thousand Master. But to do so, Negi must take a huge risk. He must study under the mysterious Evangeline, a dark mage as powerful as she is delightfully wicked.

Chapter Titles

  • 10th Period: An All-Day Date with Class Rep-san!?
  • 11th Period: Her Secret Identity Is a Net Idol!
  • 12th Period: I Have to Get Stronger!
  • 13th Period: The Sprite Shards Are Star Crystals?
  • 14th Period: No One Is Alone
  • Special Period: Mahora Sentai Baka Rangers & True Nonstop Ayaka!
name: Magic Lessons!

description:
Bushido, Babes, and Battle. What more could an aspiring samurai hope for? In the great tradition of classic fanservice manga and the inspiration for the popular Japanese anime, Samurai Harem: Asu no Yoichi stars Yoichi Karasuma, a young man from a small mountain village looking to become a great samurai. So he heads to the city to continue his training, only to find himself staying at a dojo run by four babelicious sisters! He's there to train, but Yoichi's newly awakened libido is going to make concentration more difficult than ever! Let the hijinks begin!

Chapter Titles

  • First Blade: Enter the Samurai
  • Second Blade: Welcome to Yokko High
  • Third Blade: Eager Chihaya
  • Fourth Blade: Calling All Tsunderes
name: Vol. 1

description:
ASSASSINS!!!! As his training continues, two new girls come to town looking for Yoichi. The last remaining students of a dying ninja clan, Tsubasa and Angela have one goal: Kill Yoichi in order to save their school! As the fight heats up and the clothes come off, will Yoichi be able to handle everything thrown at him? Find out as Yoichi battles two girls who put the a$$ in assassin!

Chapter Titles

  • Fifth Blade: White Knee-Socks and Black Nylons
  • Sixth Blade: Better in the Buff
  • Seventh Blade: Incredible in Bed
  • Eighth Blade: Date Training
